/* Localized name shown for the Relay input source in the macOS input menu and in
   System Settings ▸ Keyboard ▸ Input Sources.

   macOS resolves an input mode's display name by looking up its input-mode id
   (its TISInputSourceID — the ComponentInputModeDict key) as a key in this table.
   With no entry it falls back to showing the raw id (e.g.
   "com.mattworzala.inputmethod.RelayInputMethod"), which is the ugly "full group
   and name" the user sees. Both build variants' mode ids are listed so the
   installed (Release) and dev (Debug) copies each get a clean name.

   Mechanism modeled on Apple's NumberInput IMKit sample (see TN2128). */

"com.mattworzala.inputmethod.RelayInputMethod" = "Relay";
"com.mattworzala.inputmethod.RelayInputMethod.dev" = "Relay Dev";
